    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "JAMES GRIME: So recently, we had\nbig maths news, didn&#39;t we?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We had that new prime number\nthat was found.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it was the biggest prime\nnumber ever found.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it was big news.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we were all quite\nexcited about it.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It was lots of fun.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But it got me thinking about one\nof the classic proofs in", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mathematics, and that is the\nproof that there are", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "infinitely many primes.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So even though we found this\nhuge, 17-million-digit prime", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "number, it is still not the\nbiggest prime number of all.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because there&#39;s infinitely\nmany of them.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So shall we do this\nclassic proof?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;ll say before I start that\nmany of you may have seen", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this proof before.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It goes way back.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But for those who haven&#39;t seen\nit before, this is what", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mathematicians consider an\nelegant and a beautiful proof.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we&#39;re going to prove\ninfinitely many primes.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To do that, first of\nall, we&#39;re going", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to assume the opposite.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;m going to say there are\nfinitely many primes.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if there&#39;s finitely many of\nthem, we can write a list.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And let&#39;s do that.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I&#39;m going to call\nthem prime 1.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Don&#39;t know what it is\nparticularly, but let&#39;s call", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it prime 1.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Prime 2, prime 3, and I&#39;ll just\ngo on until I get to the", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "last one, which I&#39;ll\ncall prime n.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The point I want to make,\nthough, is that this is a", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "complete list.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that&#39;s important.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, the next thing\nI&#39;m going to do--", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m going to make\na new number.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s a whole number.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m going to call it Q. So let&#39;s\ncall it Q. And to make", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this number, I&#39;m going to\nmultiply all these together--", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "prime 1 times prime 2 times\nprime 3, all the way up to the", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "last one there, prime n.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there&#39;ll be only one way to\nwrite Q. As a product of", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "primes, it&#39;s a unique\nexpression.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there&#39;s only one way\nyou can write Q.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then I&#39;m going to add 1.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Q is either prime,\nor it&#39;s not.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s the only options\nit has.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If Q is prime, then it&#39;s a new\nprime that&#39;s not on this list.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s bad.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So hopefully, it&#39;s\nnot a prime.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If it&#39;s not a prime, then it\nis made up from primes by", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "multiplying primes together.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, those prime factors of\nQ will divide Q exactly.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And here&#39;s the problem--", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "none of these primes on my\nlist divide Q exactly.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They&#39;ll divide this number\nperfectly, but", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "not this plus 1 number.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You&#39;ll always have\n1 left over.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the prime factors are\nnot on this list.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this list is not complete.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I said if there&#39;s finitely many\nof them, I can have a", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "complete list.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You cannot.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s the proof\nthat there are", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "infinitely many primes.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the definition of a prime\nis that it&#39;s the building", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "blocks of other numbers.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So all other whole numbers\nare made by", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "multiplying primes together.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So Q is a whole number,\nand it is made by", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "multiplying primes together.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in this case, the problem\nis none of the primes on my", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "list do that trick.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They don&#39;t divide the\nnumber exactly.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there&#39;s primes missing.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What I&#39;ve got here is a copy\nof a book called &quot;Euclid&#39;s", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Elements.&quot; And this is a\ntextbook written by a Greek", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mathematician called Euclid.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, Euclid lived in 300 BC.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this textbook is\n2,300 years old.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s never been out of print.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s second only to the\nBible in that respect.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s one of the most important\nbooks in mathematics.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s one of the most important\nbooks in human history.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the proof that there\nare infinitely many", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "primes is in here.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I checked it out earlier.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It was on page 227, which is\nBook Nine, Proposition 20.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it is right there, the\nproof that there are", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "infinitely many primes.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There&#39;s a couple of differences\nfrom this proof to", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what I did.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One difference is my proof there\nwas something called a", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "proof by contradiction.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s something that\nmathematicians do a lot.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s really useful.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What Euclid did was slightly\ndifferent.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He assumed that there was\na list of primes.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he said, but you can\nkeep adding to it.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So you can never complete\nthe list, which is the", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "same sort of idea.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The other difference is that\nthis book was written in the", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "days before algebra.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So he didn&#39;t have algebra\nto use like I did.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So all his proofs are using\nstraight lines and circles.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it looks quite different, but\nit&#39;s actually quite easy", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to translate into\nmodern terms.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You see, mathematics is\nthe search for truth.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this book is as true today\nas it was 2,300 years ago.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We know a prime number can\nonly be divided by 1 and", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "itself, by no other factors, so\nhow did Euclid define it?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s actually in here.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I was quite excited\nwhen I found this.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So let&#39;s have a look.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In Definitions--", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "look here-- at the\nbeginning of Book", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Seven, he defines terms.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Look at that.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;A prime number is that which is\nmeasured by a unit alone.&quot;", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So only units fit into\nthe prime number.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It was all measured with lines,\nso a line with length a", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "prime can only fit\nunits into it.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can&#39;t fit 2&#39;s and 3&#39;s and\nother lengths into it.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if we had something that\nwas prime length--", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let&#39;s make it 7.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There we go--", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "then you can fit 1&#39;s into it--", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But you wouldn&#39;t be able\nto fit 2&#39;s into it.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So here&#39;s a 2.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that would not fit\ninto my length 7.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or if I tried 4&#39;s or 3&#39;s, it\nwouldn&#39;t fit into my length 7.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So a prime length would only fit\nunits into it and itself.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s the definition\nof primes we have today.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
